Naira cash rate appreciated 0.06 per cent to N359.00/$ at the parallel market on Monday, while the transfer rate remained unchanged at N363.50/$. The local currency also gained 0.02 per cent against to N306.95/$1 at the official window. The Investors and Exporters (I&E) FX window opened at N360.15, traded high at N361.65 and eventually closed at N360.83, representing a 0.01 per cent appreciation against last Friday’s closing position. A total of $367.20 million was transacted through the I&E window, while turnover fell by 55 per cent to $165 million. 